      <h3 class="title">
      <a href="/article/8732#comment-347808" class="active">wrong correction?</a>          </h3>
  
  
  <div class="picture">
  <img src="/files/linuxjournal.com/images/personicon.jpg" alt="Anonymous&#039;s picture" title="Anonymous&#039;s picture"  /></div>

  <div class="submitted">
    Submitted by Anonymous (not verified) on Tue, 01/26/2010 - 17:02.  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <p>&gt; The stdin (file descriptor 0) of the gpg process is filename txt,<br />
rather than passphrase.txt, so your (intended) passphrase is never actually used!</p>
<p>Then how come the decryption worked?</p>
      </div>

  
